TLDR: Oil/gas isnt bad, but we need to stop BURNING IT ALL. Bring back trains and stop greed based economic systems that encourage quick consumption > longevity of goods.

I know the irony of my new @Commsaur pfp being a dino is amazing, but oil/gas is not evil! It is our over utilization of the resource that is killing us. Also planned obsolescence (capitalist â€œinnovationâ€) is burning our limited metals and catalysts supplies. Soooooo complicated.

Using fossil fuels to produce goods like solar panels and computers that PRODUCE more sustainable communication and energy than the chemical process it takes to produce them is a more mid term solution, especially with â€œgreen chemistryâ€ innovations that use less harsh solvents.

I do not know the stats, but if people and transportation are not DIRECTLY dependent on fossil fuels we will have a lot more to convert into goods. I am less well versed on the chem, but polymer chemistry produces WAY LESS CO2 chemically than PHYSICALLY BURNING it in combustion.

hot take + chem: Converting oil/gas from a consumer good to a supply chain good will bring about an era of peace. Most of our modern goods, based on polymer chemistry, requires carbon. Our modern goods require fossil fuels in the supply chain, including electronics and plastics.

I regret ever trying to loose weight. I wish I just did the harder work of loving myself as I am sooner, but its never too late to start. Happy I have started and can just enjoy my life as it comes with the body that keeps me going. ğŸ’–ğŸŒˆâœŠğŸ½

We cant control our weight, so we should not bother trying. I am fat/chub and still moved my body. Could rock climb better than most skinny/muscular folks. Release the shame of fat rolls and bellies. Wear tight cloths and crop tops. Weight cycling is far far worse than being fat.

Hope someone benefits from this, but I wish I never lost weight. I was miserable when I was thin and have regained the weight back (which is typical). The reality is that being thin did not make me love myself, only loving myself did that.
